@startuml Implantacao
skinparam nodeStyle rectangle

title Diagrama de Implantação — Ambiente de Desenvolvimento / Demonstração

node "Estação do Pesquisador" as Host {
  node "Navegador Web" as Browser {
    artifact "GrafoGen\nlocalhost:5173" as WebApp
  }

  node "Node.js Runtime" as Node {
    artifact "Vite Dev Server\n:5173" as Vite
    artifact "Express API\n:3001" as API
  }

  node "Python 3.10+" as Python {
    artifact "src.app.main\n--mine | --build | --analyze" as Main
    artifact "src.app.api_demo" as Demo
    database "venv\n(requirements.txt)" as Venv
  }

  folder "Sistema de Arquivos" as Disk {
    storage "github-graph-analyzer/\ndata/raw/" as Raw
    storage "github-graph-analyzer/\noutput/graphs/" as Graphs
    storage "github-graph-analyzer/\noutput/reports/" as Reports
    storage ".env\n(GITHUB_TOKEN)" as Env
  }
}

cloud "Internet" as Net {
  node "api.github.com" as GitHub {
    artifact "REST API v3\n(issues, PRs, reviews)" as Rest
  }
}

Browser --> Vite : HTTP
Browser --> API : HTTP /api/*\n(proxy Vite)
Vite ..> API : proxy dev

API --> Main : child_process.spawn\npython -m src.app.main
Main --> Venv
Main --> Env : lê token
Main --> Raw : escreve (mine)
Main --> Graphs : escreve (build)
Main --> Reports : escreve (analyze)

API --> Raw : leitura status
API --> Graphs : serve .gexf
API --> Reports : serve csv/json

Main --> Rest : PyGithub\n(apenas --mine)
Demo --> Graphs : gera demo .gexf

note bottom of Host
  Deploy típico: tudo local na máquina do desenvolvedor.
  Produção acadêmica: mesma topologia em demo ao vivo.
end note

@enduml
